<!--25-->Lurtz&#39;s Battle Cry x2<br>
Can You Protect me From Yourself? x2    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Although this is not the deck I will use at future tournements, this is one of my 2 main decks. My other is Shoulder to Shoulder White Trash/The Mirror is Broken with Sauron Shadow.<br>
<br>
The point of this deck is to either run, or kill your opponent with Shadow. It goes like this: If it&#39;s a mirror deck, run. If it&#39;s not, pace your fellowship&#39;s little walk. This deck can run pretty easily with archery back-ups and killer people like Boromir and Aragorn while pumped up. As you might also know, this deck has a good chance against twilight nazgul, as i have plenty of cancelling skirmishes cards in here, like the staff, fili, stealths, and some more. The shadow is designed like this: Bring lurtz and Soldier out at site 4 or higher, for only 9 twilight. Soldier makes lurtz fierce + he can hold his own + he discards a card. Captain can bring back a lurtz, and that costs 11 twilight to do, plus captain&#39;s 2 more strength than soldier. However, with a lot of twilight, you can get an easy kill on some companions. Try to save 5 at the beginning (if possible), so savagery will come in handy. CYPMFY is extremely useful at site 4-5, or site 7-9. This is an option: -4 raiders and 3 assassins for 4 towers of orthanc, and 2 more troops and 1 more lieutenant, but this might leave you at a minion shortage. You want some cheap minions. I found that scouts sometimes worked. Also, Soldiers have won at least 3 games for me by THEM overwhelming Frodo or doing many wounds with battle cry. Soldiers rock. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
